<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF9CEF5FFF12F91DFCB5F95E" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF12F91DFB61F97A" blockId="52.[151,1437,1703,2019]" box="[151,1236,1703,1731]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF12F91DFE86F97A" bold="true" box="[151,307,1704,1730]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Distribution:</emphasis>
South America; Argentina: Misiones; 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFD67F91DFC9EF97A" bold="true" box="[738,811,1704,1730]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9CEF5FFD67F91DFC9EF97A" box="[738,811,1704,1730]" name="Brazil" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Brazil</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFCBFF912FC24F97A" bold="true" box="[826,913,1703,1730]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF9CEF5FFCBFF912FC24F97A" box="[826,913,1703,1730]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Paraná</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
; Colombia: Valle del Cauca.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF42F979FCB5F95E" blockId="52.[151,1437,1703,2019]" box="[199,768,1739,1766]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF42F979FCB5F95E" bold="true" box="[199,768,1739,1766]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
New record for 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9CEF5FFE06F979FE79F95E" box="[387,460,1740,1766]" name="Brazil" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and for the 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF9CEF5FFDDBF97EFD4EF95E" box="[606,763,1739,1766]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF9CEF5EFF42F945FDE0FEA5" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF42F945FC92F8EA" blockId="52.[151,1437,1703,2019]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF42F945FEE7F8B2" bold="true" box="[199,338,1776,1802]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Comments:</emphasis>
This species was also rarely found after its description. As far as we know, this is only the fourth record of the species. Just as for the other species of the tribe previously presented, 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9CEF5FFBC2F8A0FB69F896" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1869" box="[1095,1244,1812,1839]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Steirodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentiferum">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFBC2F8A0FB69F896" box="[1095,1244,1812,1839]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">S. dentiferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also seems to be broadly distributed along forested areas of South America.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF42F8E9FACFF85A" blockId="52.[151,1437,1703,2019]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF42F8E9FEEEF8CE" bold="true" box="[199,347,1884,1910]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFF9CEF5FFEEEF8E9FE59F8CF" box="[363,492,1884,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[210,1376,191,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@51.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 26. Calling songs of species of Steirodontini and of Enthephippion olivaceum. A–C: Cnemidophyllum citrifolium; D–F: Steirodon dentiferoides; G–I: S. dentiferum. A: sonogram of one echeme; B, E and H: sonogram of one syllable; D and G: sonogram of two isolated syllables; C, F and H: spectrogram of the respective syllable." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550123" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550123/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 26G–I</figureCitation>
): The stridulation is performed by males at night, when long sequences of syllables not forming echemes are produced. Similarly to sounds of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9CEF5FFC99F834FC04F822" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[796,945,1920,1947]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Cnemidophyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrifolium">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFC99F834FC04F822" box="[796,945,1920,1947]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">C. citrifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9CEF5FFC60F834FB24F822" authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1970" box="[997,1169,1920,1947]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Steirodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentiferoides">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFC60F834FC46F823" box="[997,1011,1921,1947]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFB85F835FB24F822" box="[1024,1169,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">dentiferoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, each syllable is formed by pulses that are very sparse in the beginning, then becoming more grouped after the first third of the syllable. These pulses are produced in a crescendo of intensity until the mid of stridulation, when the intensity stabilizes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9DEF5EFF42FF22FDE1FF09" blockId="53.[199,597,151,285]" box="[199,596,151,177]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9DEF5EFF42FF22FE1EFF09" box="[199,427,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Dominant frequency</emphasis>
: 10 ± 0.4 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9DEF5EFF42FF0EFE45FF6D" blockId="53.[199,597,151,285]" box="[199,496,187,213]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9DEF5EFF42FF0EFEF5FF6D" box="[199,320,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Bandwidth</emphasis>
: 6.3 ± 0.1 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9DEF5EFF42FF6AFDFBFF41" blockId="53.[199,597,151,285]" box="[199,590,222,249]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9DEF5EFF42FF6AFE9BFF40" box="[199,302,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Duration</emphasis>
: Syllable: 0.05 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFF9DEF5EFE73FF6BFDFCFF41" box="[502,585,222,249]" degrees="0.005" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" precision="55" value="-0.005">0.005 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9DEF5EFF42FEB6FDE0FEA5" blockId="53.[199,597,151,285]" box="[199,597,259,285]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9DEF5EFF42FEB6FEEAFEA5" box="[199,351,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Mute interval</emphasis>
: Syllable: 4.1 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFF9DEF5EFD9CFEB6FDE5FEA5" box="[537,592,259,285]" degrees="0.9" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" precision="5555" value="-0.9">0.9 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
